250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
340 g Pizza Dough
1 unit Green Bell Pepper
1 unit Shallot
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
6 g Lemon-Pepper Seasoning
30 g Mixed Olives
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, remove pizza dough from fridge and rest in a warm spot for 20 min. Wash and dry all produce.
Preheat the oven to 450˚F.
Lightly coat dough with oil. Divide dough into 2 (4) equal pieces.
Using oiled hands, stretch each piece into a rough oval shape on a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets.)
Let dough rest in a warm place for 8-10 min.

While dough rests, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then sausage. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up sausage into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with Lemon-Pepper Seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce base. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant.
Add 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.

Meanwhile, peel, then thinly slice shallot.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Drain olives, then roughly chop.
With oiled hands, stretch dough again into a large oval shape. (NOTE: Dough should now hold its shape.)
Spread pesto over dough.
Spread sausage mixture over dough.
Top with peppers, olives and shallots.
Sprinkle mozzarella and feta over top.

Bake in the middle of the oven for 14-18 min, until browned and crisp. (NOTE: For 4 servings, bake pizzas in the middle and top of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

When pizza is done, let sit for 2-3 min.
Cut pizza into slices, then drizzle yogurt sauce over top.
Divide pizza between plates.